    "body": "The z-values in these two grids are the same, but I would expect to have the z-values scaled by 10^-4 (``-Gtest.nc+s0.0001``) in the second grid. \r\n\r\nSame behaviour in `grdproject`.\r\n\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ gmt grdcut @earth_relief_30m -Gtest.nc -RNO\r\n\r\n$ gmt grdinfo test.nc\r\ntest.nc: Title: Produced by grdcut\r\ntest.nc: Command: grdcut @earth_relief_30m_p -Gtest.nc -RNO\r\ntest.nc: Remark: Obtained by Gaussian Cartesian filtering (55.6 km fullwidth) from SRTM15+V2.1.nc [Tozer et al., 2019; http://dx.doi.org/10.1029/2019EA000658]\r\ntest.nc: Pixel node registration used [Geographic grid]\r\ntest.nc: Grid file format: nf = GMT netCDF format (32-bit float), CF-1.7\r\ntest.nc: x_min: -9.5 x_max: 34 x_inc: 0.5 (30 min) name: longitude n_columns: 87\r\ntest.nc: y_min: 57.5 y_max: 81.5 y_inc: 0.5 (30 min) name: latitude n_rows: 48\r\ntest.nc: v_min: -4271 v_max: 1409.5 name: elevation (m) <---------------------------------------- identical!\r\ntest.nc: scale_factor: 1 add_offset: 0\r\ntest.nc: format: classic\r\n\r\n$ gmt grdcut @earth_relief_30m -Gtest.nc+s0.0001 -RNO\r\n\r\n$ gmt grdinfo test.nc\r\ntest.nc: Title: Produced by grdcut\r\ntest.nc: Command: grdcut @earth_relief_30m_p -Gtest.nc+s0.0001 -RNO\r\ntest.nc: Remark: Obtained by Gaussian Cartesian filtering (55.6 km fullwidth) from SRTM15+V2.1.nc [Tozer et al., 2019; http://dx.doi.org/10.1029/2019EA000658]\r\ntest.nc: Pixel node registration used [Geographic grid]\r\ntest.nc: Grid file format: nf = GMT netCDF format (32-bit float), CF-1.7\r\ntest.nc: x_min: -9.5 x_max: 34 x_inc: 0.5 (30 min) name: longitude n_columns: 87\r\ntest.nc: y_min: 57.5 y_max: 81.5 y_inc: 0.5 (30 min) name: latitude n_rows: 48\r\ntest.nc: v_min: -4271 v_max: 1409.5 name: elevation (m) <--------------------------------------- identical!\r\ntest.nc: scale_factor: 0.0001 add_offset: 0 packed z-range: [-42710000,14095000]\r\ntest.nc: format: classic\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe related to the direct use of `@earth_relief`? So tried:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ gmt grdcut -RNO test.nc -Gno.nc+s0.0001\r\n\r\n$ gmt grdinfo no.nc \r\nno.nc: Title: Produced by grdcut\r\nno.nc: Command: grdcut -RNO test.nc -Gno.nc+s0.0001\r\nno.nc: Remark: Obtained by Gaussian Cartesian filtering (55.6 km fullwidth) from SRTM15+V2.1.nc [Tozer et al., 2019; http://dx.doi.org/10.1029/2019EA000658]\r\nno.nc: Pixel node registration used [Geographic grid]\r\nno.nc: Grid file format: nf = GMT netCDF format (32-bit float), CF-1.7\r\nno.nc: x_min: -9.5 x_max: 34 x_inc: 0.5 (30 min) name: longitude n_columns: 87\r\nno.nc: y_min: 57.5 y_max: 81.5 y_inc: 0.5 (30 min) name: latitude n_rows: 48\r\nno.nc: v_min: -4271 v_max: 1409.5 name: elevation (m)\r\nno.nc: scale_factor: 0.0001 add_offset: 0 packed z-range: [-42710000,14095000]\r\nno.nc: format: classic\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut same here; no scaling takes place.",
