            "body": "That is not what **+s** does on output.  It scales the values alright but also sets the scale factor (see it is not 1 but changed to 0.0001).  The purpose of all this is to be able to scale data to integers and save on the space.  All the remote grids are stored as various short int grids with different scales and offsets so as to minimize size and download.  Not only that, those grids are stored as JPEG 2000 tiles to minimize file size further.\r\n",
